@node "Preview_Window" "Preview Window"
The Preview Window is not yet implemented.

1.x releases will not have a WYSYWYG builder and without preview window.

2.x will have a preview window, but not WYSYWYG.

3.x WYSYWYG

@endnode

@node "Edit_Window" "Edit Window"

@{b}The Edit Window@{ub}


It's the main window. You have the main functions inside.

At the top, you have the name of file and its status :
- Modified , you have made changes in the buffer.
- Opened , you have just opened a file.
- Saved, the buffer is saved to the named filename.

@{u}4 buttons :@{uu}
- New  replaces the current buffer to a sample HTML sheet.
- Open opens a file by a ASL window.
- Save saves the current buffer to the named filename.
- Save as  saves the the current buffer to the other named filename.

@{u}The next group has :@{uu}
- @{"Font Cycle Gadget" link "CY_Font_Edit" 0}
- 11 buttons :
  * B puts the selected text into bold style.
  * I puts the selected text into italic style.
  * u puts the selected text into underlined style.
  * left right center justify aligned text.
  * @{"Hyper links" link "Hyper_Window" 0}
  * @{"Markup window" link "Markup_Window" 0}
  * insert a sample Horizontal rule.
  * insert a list item.

@{u}The Buffer:@{uu}
It uses a special gadget the textfield gadget, so, the buffer
operations are under its control. 

You can type, insert, cut, paste text by classic hotkeys (A-c A-v).

If you typed :
This is an example

You want to put in bold style, you @{b}must@{ub} select the text and
choose the Bold gadget.

@{bg shine}All tag operations must have a selected text@{bg back}, if not, you can have
things like this:
<B><B>This is an example</B>This is an example</B>

It's also an @{"app-window" link "Type_Window" 0}...

@{b}If you use MagicMenu and/or CycleMenu, please install SafeGIRPort, the
patch for not to have a frozen system.@{ub}
@endnode

@node "CY_Font_Edit" "Font Cycle Gadget"
@{b}The Font Cycle Gadget@{ub}

Instead of to go into menu item to change style font, choose one of
different types and hit the "Apply" button.

@{u}There is 2 special entries:@{uu}
- ISO-Latin->Entities replaces all iso-latin letters by its
  alphanumeric entities, ex : Ú -> &eacute;

- Entities->ISO-Latin in the other way.
In fact, these 2 features are toggle together.

See also the @{"tooltypes" link "Tooltypes" 0} section.

- WebMaker doesn't convert some letters such as > and < , guess why ?

@endnode 


@node "Colors_Window" "Link Colors Window"

@{b}The Link Colors Window@{ub}

This window is to set the BODY parameters.

- You can have a background picture. Show it to see if it is good. A
@{"preview window" link "Picture_Window" 0} is opened to see it.

- Choose which color is in the BODY.

- Adjust with the colorwheel, but selected which colors before.

@endnode

@node "Tables_Window" "Tables"

@{b}Tables@{ub}

Making and understanding tables is not an easy stuff and which Web
Navigator shows them correctly under Amiga ???

I will make tables in other building way.

@endnode

@node "Image_Window" "Image Window"

@{b}The Image Window@{ub}

Choose your picture, you can selected the align option. Set the
alternate text for text-clients like Alynx. Set the picture width,
height, very useful. If you choose a gif picture, hit "show" and the
width, height will be set.

Hit ok to insert the line.

@endnode

@node "Hyper_Window" "HyperLink Window"

@{b}The HyperLink Window@{ub}

When a file is opened, its links are added to the hyper-links
listview. Double-Click to set the string gadget, choose the type of
hyper-links. Hit the associated text links, or double-click in the
textlinks listview. You can load a file to add links to the actual
list, and save the links into named file.

See also the @{"tooltypes" link "ToolTypes" 0} section.

@endnode

@node "HR_Window" "Horizontal Line"

@{b}Horizontal Line@{ub}

This window allows you to make all types of HR and their options.

@endnode

@node "Type_Window" "File Window"

@{b}The File Window@{ub}

This window appears when you drop a file into the @{"Edit Window" link
"Edit_Window" 0}.

You must choose the type of the dropped file.
If it's a link, its name is added to the hyper-link window.

@endnode

@node "Quit_Window" "Quit Window"

@{b}The Quit Window@{ub}

The buffer is altered, but not saved, so you have this window. Choose
what you want to do "Quit" without save, "Save and Quit" "Cancel"

@endnode

@node "Picture_Window" "Picture Window"

@{b}The Picture Window@{ub}

Show your pictures, inlined or background before. The resolution is
limited but it's very useful to see background patterns.

@endnode

@node "Project_Window" "Project Window"

@{b}The Project Window@{ub}

When WebMaker is running, 2 @{"tooltypes" link "ToolTypes" 0} set the gadget strings.

Server Root Local is your local html doc path such as http:docs
Server Root Distant is the path in the HTML document.

If a reference file has the local path, it will be replaced by the
distant root path. Example :

- Server Root Local is http:docs/
- Server Root Distant is /

So a reference file such as http:docs/foo/bar.html is replaced by :
/foo/bar.html

In next releases, the project window will have more features such as a
document title string, color links, and other stuffs like RCS
revision, author, notes.

When you open a HTML document, all these parameters will be adjusted.
The Edit window will be only the body document.
@{"See this in 1.2 release." SYSTEM "Sys:utilities/Multiview /demos/project.iff"}

@endnode

@node "Markup_Window" "Markup Window"

@{b}The Markup Window@{ub}

A markup is a tag to mark a place in the document. The mark is added
to the hyperlinks listview.

@endnode

@node "Warning_Window" "Warning Window"

@{b}The Warning Window@{ub}

If you have this window, you have made some changes and you want to
open a file, or new sample sheet.

@endnode

@node "Search_Window" "Search Window"

@{b}The Search Window@{ub}

The search is made from the beginning of the buffer.

@endnode

@node "ToolTypes" "ToolTypes"

For setting, tooltypes are an easy way.

Differents tooltypes are available :

@{b}LOCALROOT@{ub}=http:docs/                  
Set your local HTML doc root

@{b}DISTANTROOT@{ub}=                        
Set your distant root. See the @{"project window" link "Project_Window" 0}.

@{b}AUTHOR@{ub}=Pascal Rullier
Set the default author name.

@{b}EMAIL@{ub}=prullier@mail.atlantic-line.fr
Set the default email author.

@{b}SPECIAL@{ub}=This is a special thing     
See its use in 1.2 release in the @{"project window" link "Project_Window" 0}.

@{b}RCS@{ub}=$$
Set the RCS pattern.

@{b}LINKSFILE@{ub}=http:docs/hyperlinks.wmhl
Set your hyper-links file.

@{b}LINKSTEXTFILE@{ub}=http:docs/textlinks.whtl
Set your text links file.

@{b}ISOBUFFER@{ub}=YES
If set to YES, an entities<->iso operation is made.
So you have entities in file, the buffer is in iso mode.

@{b}ENTITIESSAVING@{ub}=YES
if set to YES, an entities<->iso operation is made.
So if your buffer has iso letters, it will be saved with entities.

@endnode
